✨✨Eye makeup tips for Hooded Eyes ✨✨

✅ Focus on the outer lid are above the crease
✅ Use of neutral shadows is preferred to make lid area look larger
✅ use the similar neutral shade but a bit darker to create depth will give illusion of bigger eyes 
✅ Always apply the shimmer or glitter shade from the centre and blend it out wards. Don’t forget to take it a bit above the actual crease.
✅ Applying the liner with wing and pointed inner corner make the eyes look elongated.
✅ Always apply the mascara for volume & length for a fuller lash. 
.
.
.
I have used @gush.beauty eyeshadow stack to create the  eye look because the eyeshadows are so pigmented and super easy to use. The stack is enough to create day to evening eye makeup look as it’s a perfect combination of mattes and shimmers. They are travel friendly too due to its compact packaging.
